{"author":{"id":"aed0d72ca16b13a779b1d37a0771f1682d5a59e673ecfbcdd34155713180df84"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1636125858,"nonce":"dPeVuLsY1TbY5T5iEcOVad/jA9M=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOD3p2KM4-WD5X","github-url":"https://github.com/OPEN-NEXT/OKH-LOSH/issues/107","origin":"github"},"title":"Standard for the language field(s)","message":"Neither OKH v1 nor we specify this further, as much as I know.\nwithout this... that field becomes somewhat unusable, as there are many standards out there, and if people assume different standards, there will be errors, or filtering and searching will lead to incomplete results.\n\naccording to my research, it would make most sense to use this standard:\n\nhttps://www.w3.org/International/articles/language-tags/\n\nIt is [IETF's BCP 47](http://www.rfc-editor.org/rfc/bcp/bcp47.txt), but nicely and colorfully explained, and it shows that it is the standard in XML, HTML (plus probably most other technical formats ... in POSIX it is too, for example).\nconveniently, it is also includes what we are already using in the TOML files out there.","files":null}]}